## ✅ PHASE 4 — Code Intelligence (Lightweight)
### Goal: Symbols outline, go-to-line, go-to-symbol, recent files

**4.1 Symbols / outline panel** ✅
- ✅ "Outline" sidebar panel
- ✅ Client-side regex parsing per language:
  - ✅ JS/TS: function, class, const arrow functions, methods
  - ✅ CSS: selectors, at-rules
  - ✅ HTML: id attributes, landmark tags
  - ✅ Python: def, class
  - ✅ JSON: top-level keys
  - ✅ Markdown: headings
- ✅ Click symbol → jumps editor to line
- ✅ Updates on tab switch (called from _activateTab)

**4.2 Go-to-line** ✅
- ✅ Ctrl+G → modal input "Go to line:"
- ✅ Accepts line:col format (e.g. 42:8)
- ✅ Jumps editor to position

**4.3 Go-to-symbol** ✅
- ✅ Ctrl+Shift+O → dedicated `#goto-symbol-modal` fuzzy search modal
- ✅ Reads symbols from current file's `_outlineCache`
- ✅ Real-time filter as you type, arrow key navigation, Enter to jump
- ✅ Shows symbol kind icon, name, line number
- ✅ Jumps editor to line + selects symbol text
- ✅ Also available via command palette entry "Go to Symbol…"

**4.4 Recent files** ✅
- ✅ _trackRecent() logs last opened files
- ✅ Recent files shown at top of command palette

**Acceptance:** ✅ Outline updates live. Go-to-line + Go-to-symbol both work. Recent files in palette.

